{"pageProps":{"seo":{"title":"","description":"","keywords":"","image":"https://static.pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/main_home.jpg"},"content":{"title":"","description":""},"isWorkCase":true,"workCase":{"id":2255,"name":"Kaikas","shortdescription":"Browser Extension for Running DApps","description":"Chrome, Firefox and Opera browser extension for running DApps, authorizing and sending transactions, and managing your online wallet.","preview":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/work-browser-extension-for-running-dapps-1920.jpg","preview500":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/work-browser-extension-for-running-dapps-544.jpg","preview768":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/work-browser-extension-for-running-dapps-1024.jpg","alt":"The screenshot of UI of Kaikas on a mobile phone","sections":[{"acf_fc_layout":"headdescription","button_text":"Share your idea","shortdescription":"Browser Extension for Running DApps","description":"Chrome, Firefox and Opera browser extension for running DApps, authorizing and sending transactions, and managing your online wallet\r\n","project_heading":"","project_goal":"","technologyheading":"Work Done","technologiestags":[{"entry":"Browser extension for Chrome, Firefox, and Opera "},{"entry":"Online wallet for Klaytn blockchain"},{"entry":"UI and functionality for DApp connection"},{"entry":"<a href=\"https://pixelplex.io/quality-assurance/\">QA testing</a> for multiple browsers"}],"tags":[{"value":"Blockchain","label":"Blockchain"},{"value":"Web","label":"Web"},{"value":"Smart Contracts","label":"Smart Contracts"},{"value":"DApps","label":"DApps"},{"value":"Blockchain Consulting","label":"Blockchain Consulting"}]},{"acf_fc_layout":"solutions","technologies":[{"title":"React","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/react_icon.svg","alt":"React icon"}},{"title":"Node.js","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/node.svg","alt":"Node icon"}},{"title":"EthereumJS","image":false},{"title":"web3.js","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/web3d_icon.svg","alt":"Web3D icon"}},{"title":"caver-js","image":false},{"title":"BigNumber.js","image":false},{"title":"Redux","image":false},{"title":"BIP39","image":false},{"title":"Ramda","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/ramada_icon.svg","alt":"Ramada icon"}},{"title":"Lodash","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/lodash_icon.svg","alt":"Lodash icon"}},{"title":"Gulp","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/gulp_icon.svg","alt":"Gulp.js icon"}},{"title":"ESLint","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/eslint_icon.svg","alt":"ESLint icon"}},{"title":"Babel","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/babel_icon.svg","alt":"Bable icon"}}],"rows":[{"title":"<h2>Solution</h2>\n","text":"<p>Kaikas is a browser extension acting as a web wallet and interface for regular users to have access to the Klaytn network. <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was designed as an equivalent of Metamask extension with added functionality and user-friendly interface, allowing to seamlessly connect with Klaytn DApps, authorize and send transactions, and manage your <a href=\"https://pixelplex.io/cryptocurrency-exchange-development/\">cryptocurrency web wallet</a>.</span> The extension was developed for Chrome, Firefox, and Opera browsers.</p>\n"}]},{"acf_fc_layout":"twocolumnstext","description_top":"","slides":[{"image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/kaikas-slide-1-1600.jpg","alt":"The transaction process of Kaikas platform"},"image_768":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/kaikas-slide-1-768.jpg","image_500":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/kaikas-slide-1-500.jpg","image_320":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/kaikas-slide-1-320.jpg"},{"image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/kaikas-slide-2-1600.jpg","alt":"Token list, transaction history, and account details of Kaikas platform"},"image_768":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/kaikas-slide-2-768.jpg","image_500":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/kaikas-slide-2-500.jpg","image_320":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/kaikas-slide-2-320.jpg"},{"image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/kaikas-slide-3-1600.jpg","alt":"Transaction authorization, and a list of added tokens of Kaikas platform"},"image_768":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/kaikas-slide-3-768.jpg","image_500":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/kaikas-slide-3-500.jpg","image_320":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/kaikas-slide-3-320.jpg"}],"rows":[{"title":"<h3>Client</h3>\n","text":"<p><b>Ground X</b> is the blockchain subsidiary of Korea’s largest mobile service provider, Kakao, with over 50 million active users. By developing a scalable platform providing a multitude of services through its DApps, Ground X aspires to substantiate the value and utility of blockchain technology.</p>\n<p>Ground X has its own functional open-source blockchain, Klaytn. The platform provides an enterprise-friendly environment for developers to work on the creation of <a href=\"https://pixelplex.io/blockchain-development/\">blockchain services</a> and <a href=\"https://pixelplex.io/dapp-development/\">DApps</a>. Having recently launched Klaytn Mainnet, the company was faced with a problem of not having an interface for average users to interact with Klaytn and explore its vast possibilities.</p>\n"}],"title":"Details"},{"acf_fc_layout":"call_to_action","title":"Got an idea? Let’s work together","button_text":"Get in touch","background_rgb":"#64C7B4"},{"acf_fc_layout":"projectFeatures","title":"Project features","content":[{"title":"ERC-20 / ERC-721 token support","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/erc-20-erc-721-token-support.svg","alt":"Blue icon of a coin inside of a gear"}},{"title":"Password sign-in and application auto-lock","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/password-sign-in-and-app-auto-lock.svg","alt":"Blue icon of a person and password line"}},{"title":"Seed phrase as forget password feature to restore access","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/seed-phrase-as-forget-password-feature.svg","alt":"Blue icon of password line"}},{"title":"Multicurrency and multiple account management","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/multicurrency-and-multiple-account-management.svg","alt":"Blue icon of two banknotes"}},{"title":"Account nicknames to substitute addresses","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/account-nicknames-to-substitute-addresses.svg","alt":"Blue icon of two chat clouds"}},{"title":"Account QR code generation and sharing","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/account-qr-code-generation-and-sharing.svg","alt":"Blue icon of QR code processing"}},{"title":"Account balance display in KLAY and other tokens","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/account-balance-display-in-klay-and-other-tokens.svg","alt":"Blue icon of a wallet with an eye image on its surface"}},{"title":"Account transaction history","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Account-transaction-history.svg","alt":"Blue icon of a quill pen and a document"}},{"title":"Data wiping and account log-out","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/data-wiping-and-account-log-out.svg","alt":"Blue icon of a person with a crossmark instead of a face"}},{"title":"Signing/sending transactions and transaction notifications","image":{"url":"https://pixelplex.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/signing-sending-transactions-and-transaction-notifications.svg","alt":"Blue icon of a document and a coin"}},{"